.<img width="867" height="846" class="wp-image-1865175" style="width: 800px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-07-07-at-8.46.58-PM.jpeg" alt="" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-07-07-at-8.46.58-PM.jpeg?width=867&amp;auto_optimize=medium 867w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-07-07-at-8.46.58-PM-300x293.jpeg?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-07-07-at-8.46.58-PM-768x749.jpeg?width=768&amp;auto_optimize=medium 768w" sizes="(max-width: 867px) 100vw, 867px" /> …Calls for calm, says no cause for alarm By Festus Ahon, ASABA SPEAKER of the Delta State House of Assembly, Rt Hon Sheriff Oborevwori, Thursday, said he would appeal the Federal High Court Judgement, which was against his candidature for the 2023 gubernatorial election in the State. Oborevwori in a statement by his Chief Press Secretary, Mr Dennis Otu, said: “I wish to appeal to all my supporters, political associates and well wishers to remain calm and law abiding over the Judgement of the Federal Court. There is no need to panic, all is well. We will certainly appeal the Judgement and so let us maintain the peace as all hope is not lost. All is well and it will end in praise to the Glory of God Almighty. “The courts have always been part of our democratic experience ,and our confidence in the judiciary which is the last hope of the common man is unwaivering. So , as we embark on the appeal process, our supporters and indeed Deltans should kindly note and be rest assured that Rt. Hon. Sheriff Francis Orhowedor Oborevwori remains the Gubernatorial Flag Bearer of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Delta State for the 2023 general Elections. “The Sherrification Movement is well and alive and, by God’s grace, we shall overcome. Once again, I want to appreciate God Almighty for giving us victory at all times, and we will certainly not stop praying for more victories because Delta State is in God’s hands and be reassured that He will take us to the Promised Land at the end of the day. We also wish to thank our teaming supporters for their steadfastness”. A Federal High Court sitting in Abuja had today passed a judgement against the candidacy of Rt Hon Sheriff Oborevwori for the 2023 gubernatorial elections in Delta State.    Oborevwori Says No Cause For Alarm, To Appeal Judgement The Speaker of the Delta State House of Assembly and governorship candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Hon. Sheriff Oborevwori has called on all his supporters to remain calm over the Judgement of the Federal High Court, Abuja in respect… In "News" DEPUTY Speaker of the Delta State House of Assembly, Rt. Hon Christopher Ochor, Thursday, described the victory of the Speaker of the State House of Assembly, Rt Hon Sheriff Oborevwori at the gubernatorial primary election of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP in the State as well deserved.  In "News" SPEAKER of DELTA State House of Assembly, Rt Hon Sheriff Oborevwori, Tuesday, received the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP Certificate of Return as gubernatorial candidate of the party in the State.  In "News"